To make SEDutil USB 
  Got to--> https://sedutil.com/ 
  then download 
  Transfer Rescue image to the USB stick with a program like Balena Etcher
  Restart your computer, enter the BIOS, and disable secure boot
  Boot the USB thumb drive with the rescue system on it. You will see the Login prompt, enter "root" there is no password so you will get a root shell prompt.
  Enter the command: sedutil-cli --scan 
      Expected Output: will show drive path, opal type and drive name
  Enter the following command to query a specific drive: sedutil-cli --query {drive} 
  Look at the query output and make certain that the Locking section shows lockingEnabled=N
                Example:
                  -----
                  Locking function (0x0002)
                  Locked = N, LockingEnabled = N, LockingSupported = Y,
                  ---------
  Remove OPAL:
    sedutil-cli --reverttper {SIDpassword} {drive}
  Expected output:
    #sedutil-cli --reverttper debug /dev/nvme0
    - 14:23:13.968 INFO: revertTper completed successfully

Othere commands:
--yesIreallywanttoERASEALLmydatausingthePSID <PSID> <device>
revert the device using the PSID. *ERASING* *ALL* the data

Example: 
Root (to login)
sedutil-cli --scan
sedutil-cli --query /dev/nvme0
sedutil-cli --yesIreallywanttoERASEALLmydatausingthePSID <PSID> /dev/nvme0
sedutil-cli --initialSetup <newSIDpassword> /dev/nvme0
